caption: I really wanted to try this place every time I go but the lady there seems rude and is always out of things that I want. I asked for mango sticky rice once and she said she “didn’t sell/have.” Then I went specifically for the summer rolls and she said “she only had curry.” Not to sure why she never has these things but was very disappointed.
I ordered a chicken penang and the chicken felt undercooked. I ate as much as I could but threw away most of it because I didnt want to end up sick
Fantastic! Made from scratch to make it vegetarian (no fish sauce as well). Lovely hospitality
They are pretty firendly and serving Laosian style Thaifood. I had the som tum papaya salad, It smells fishy sauce too much but I liked it.

(Translated by Google) Satisfaction with taste, volume and cospa. However, it takes a lot of time from order to completion, so if you can, we recommend that you pick up after ordering by phone.  (Original) 味、ボリューム、コスパ大満足。ただオーダーから出来上がりまでが結構時間かかるので、出来れば電話でオーダーしてからピックアップするのをオススメします。
We ordered the vegan version of the Tom Yum soup and it was super yummy 😋.  We also tried the pad thai and the portion was big and very delicious. Definitely we will visit again.

TOTAL surprise to taste the MOST delicious Tom Yum Chicken soup I have had in probably more than 10 years.  The taste reminds me why this soup is so special when made well.  Very generous portion by volume and amount of chicken.

This place is pretty good and some amazing dishes.  It was a bit confusing at first. The dishes on the main board don't have any description, but they have a printed menu that does once you find it at the order station.  It might help a bit if they redid their menu board with pictures and then have a larger color plastic menu at the order station to make it a little easier to figure out what to order especially if you are unfamiliar with the dishes or don't know the differences between them.  I ordered the Kao Poon, a Laotian dish that was over the top with great flavors.  It was like a combination of Thai soups and curries in a dish that mixed them all.  I got it with shrimp and they to my surprise, didn't cook it in advance which left the shrimp delicate and juicy and not hard and over cooked when places use precooked shrimp.  It was not to thin yet not to then with the broth and with the noodles and cabbage, left you feeling satisfied.  You can tell this was a family business by the motherly types in the kitchen making sure the younger ones running the orders where in check.  They are all very friendly and made sure I was satisfied with my meal.  I do plan to go back again and check out some of their other dishes. I was very happy to see this place stay authentic and not watered down for Westerners' which drives me crazy with a lot of Asian places. Check it out, you won't be disappointed!

Absolutely delicious food! Vegetarian friendly. Great prices - the red and yellow curries are amazing!! We always get them with tofu and sticky rice. The owner is a lovely woman who is so nice. Food is always fresh and hot. Definitely worth a visit!!
